This paper proposes a deep learning model for forecasting air pollution concentrations, which involves dealing with complicated non-linear spatial and temporal correlations. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
